# Mindful Breathing Visualizer

[![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-blue.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT) 
[![GitHub contributors](https://img.shields.io/github/contributors/philgear/breathing-animation.svg)](https://github.com/philgear/breathing-animation/graphs/contributors)
[![GitHub stars](https://img.shields.io/github/stars/philgear/breathing-animation.svg)](https://github.com/philgear/breathing-animation/stargazers)

This open-source project aims to create a visually engaging and customizable tool to guide users through various breathing exercises, promoting mindfulness, relaxation, and stress reduction. It is designed to be **framework-agnostic**, allowing developers to easily integrate it into their projects, regardless of the frontend technology they are using.

## Project Goals

* **Promote mindful breathing:** Encourage users to develop a regular breathing practice.
* **Provide visual guidance:** Use animations to make breathing exercises more engaging and easier to follow.
* **Offer customization:** Allow users to personalize their experience by adjusting breathing patterns, animation styles, and other settings.
* **Foster accessibility:** Ensure the project is accessible to users with diverse needs and abilities.
* **Framework-agnostic:**  Provide flexibility for integration with any JavaScript framework or library (React, Vue, Angular, vanilla JavaScript, etc.).
* **Build a community:** Encourage collaboration and contributions from developers and users.

## Features

* **Breathing Exercises:**
    * Box breathing
    * Diaphragmatic breathing
    * Alternate nostril breathing
    * 4-7-8 breathing
* **Animation Styles:**
    * Expanding/contracting shapes (lungs, diaphragm)
    * Flowing particles or waves
    * Changing colors and gradients
* **Customization:**
    * Breathing pace and duration
    * Animation speed and colors
    * Backgrounds and themes
* **Accessibility:**
    * Alternative text descriptions for animations
    * Colorblind-friendly palettes
    * Keyboard navigation
* **Additional Features (Potential):**
    * Progress tracking
    * Reminders
    * Soundscapes
    * Biofeedback integration

This project will provide different ways to integrate the breathing animations into your project:

* **Pure JavaScript:**  A simple JavaScript API to create and control animations without any dependencies.
* **Web Components:**  Encapsulated components that can be easily used in any framework.
* **React Component:** A React component for seamless integration with React applications.
* **Vue Component:** A Vue component for use in Vue.js projects.
* **Angular Component:** An Angular component for integration with Angular applications.

## Getting Started

```bash
git clone git clone https://github.com/philgear/breathing-animation.git
cd breathing-animation
npm install 
# or
yarn install
